        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 3 at 11:40AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 1140 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Nutbush, or 8 miles southeast of Ripley, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brownsville, Ripley, Nutbush, Belle Eagle, Allens, Christmasville,
Orysa, Rudolph, Tibbs, Sunnyhill, Durhamville, Oakview, Turnpike, Owl
City, Edward Grove, and Toulon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
